      "content": "Goblin lairs are all about clever hiding spots and unexpected treasures, after all. Now, let's focus on finding the perfect accent color for your call-to-action buttons.\n\nFor high-contrast accent colors that will stand out against your deep navy blue, I recommend the following options:\n\n- #FFC107 (a vibrant, golden orange that adds a sense of energy and urgency)\n- #8BC34A (a bright, lime green that injects a pop of freshness and excitement)\n- #FF69B4 (a bold, magenta pink that adds a touch of sophistication and playfulness)\n\nWhen choosing an accent color, consider the emotions and actions you want to evoke in your users. For example, if you're creating a button that encourages users to take a bold step, like \"Open Account,\" a brighter, more energetic color like #FFC107 might be more effective. On the other hand, if you're creating a button that requires a sense of caution or attention, like \"Transfer Funds,\" a more muted, yet still striking, color like #8BC34A could be a better fit.\n\nRemember, the key is to find a balance between contrast and readability. You want your accent color to stand out, but",
